Here is the translation strings which include "customer" on TAC: https://translations.atlassian.com/dashboard/translate?lang=ja_JP#/195/0/undefined/ALL/ALL/customer
I could do the work by myself, but that is too much to do by manual. I'm wondering if there is any way to do it in bulk

Currently, Cloud products don't currently support the installation of language packs from Atlassian Translations however since we are now moving from server to cloud, this is essential.

Specific use case -
{code:java}
In Jira Server, we use customized language packages for Catalá, and Gallego which are Spanish regional languages.
Is there a way to support these languages in the Jira cloud? Any solution for this?{code}
